{1: '1', 2: 'Vera', 3: 'Time to say goodbye.', 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'King', 3: 'Dammit, why? Vera, Camu, why did you betray me!? I promised you a victory!', 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Vera', 3: 'We never need someone else to "promise" our victory. Oh, and it was Camu who proposed the betrayal. I\'m all but a pathetic, weak woman.', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Camu?', 3: '12', 4: 'Did you just call yourself a weak woman...?', 5: '13'}
{2: 'Vera', 3: 'Yeah. Never thought that all-black guy would have the same thought as you did.', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Vera', 3: 'I was joking, but it still hurts to hear you say that. Want me to show you my female side later?', 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Camu', 3: 'Cut your nonsense... I never asked you to agree with me, Vera.', 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'King', 3: 'Is that why you set me up? You filthy heroes!', 4: '1'}
{3: "The King was at his wit's end. He knew running was not an option. Everyone clenched their weapons, preparing for the last fight."}
{1: '1', 2: 'Lee', 3: 'Sorry for asking, Goddess, but are you absolutely sure that this time there will be no problem at all?', 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Goddess', 3: "Can you trust me a little? I don't care what this Celica does, but I am the Goddess of this Land of Overlord!", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Goddess', 3: 'And I never lie!', 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Kamui', 3: 'Um... Now that you mention it, did you name the "Land of Overlord" after your nickname...', 4: '1'}
{3: "Kamui seemed to find out the truth of this game, but he immediately shut up when he saw Celica's face."}
{1: '1', 2: 'King', 3: "Tsk, fine. Let's do this. Even if you have this main quest, you are still no match for me!", 4: '1'}
{2: 'King', 3: "I have accumulated unlimited data for my dream. How can I lose to you heroes, who don't even bother to level up?", 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Lee', 3: 'He has a point. We have never purposely leveled up ourselves...', 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Lucia', 3: 'But we are still heroes. Right, Commandant?', 4: '1'}
{2: "You're right.", 3: '37', 4: "Let's beat the King!", 5: '37'}
{1: '1', 2: 'King', 3: 'Bring it on, heroes!', 4: '1'}
